			<Description>Askari Mounted Archer</Description>
			<Civilopedia>The Seljuq army relied on archers and their hit-and-run tactics. Alp Arslan's army also employed light cavalry equipped with bows. They presumably exhausted the enemy's heavy cavalry by using hit-and-run tactics. Ambushes were also common. These tactics allowed the Seljuqs to defeat the Byzantines in the Battle of Manzikert. In this battle, the army was organized into a crescent formation. The centre would withdraw while the 'wings' of the crescent would surround the Byzantine army while the Seljuq archers attacked the enemy.</Civilopedia>
			<Strategy>The Askari Mounted Archer replaces the Chariot Archer. Unlike the Chariot Archer, the Askari Mounted Archer does not lose all of its [ICON_MOVES] Movement Points when entering Rough Terrain. It may also move after attacking. May choose a Double Attack promotion when promoted for the second time.</Strategy>
